"Kill or capture?" Craith asked, watching as they moved.
"It looks like capture," Cohren suspected, as the two Sentinels disappeared in the ash and smoke cloud. Yells and gunshots echoed from the hill, but soon faded away. Shortly after, the two Sentinels returned, dragging someone behind them whose boots left tracks in the ground. After retreating back to the protection of the Zug, they threw the figure onto the ground. It groaned in pain as it landed hard in the mud and snow.
Shaw approached the figure that was just trying to stand up. Then he turned to one of the Sentinels. "How many?"
"Three dead, sir," the Sentinel replied. "The rest fled on foot."
Shaw nodded and turned to Cohren and Craith, who stood nearby. "Get this guy out of my sight!"
